Since when did Starbucks employees get so persnickety about whether I need to use a straw to drink my drink?  The sippy cups for iced drinks sucks. Unless you gulp it down fast, you spend nearly the entire drink after the first few sips drinking milky water cause all the flavor is at the bottom.  Not fun.  And so now, faced with needing to hurry and finish my drink and some tooth sensitivities trying to suck it down out of the sippy top hole with the ice getting in the way, I am met with obvious animosity from the female barista from whom I asked for said straw. I was a bit taken aback when she barked at me "what was your drink" to which I replied "one that requires me to have a straw to finish it"  She was quite belligerent when another barista said that she should give me a straw and proceeded to go on and on about how inconvenient it would be to give everyone who asked for one a straw should she be working at the bar on her own and if people could just have straws willy-nilly why not leave them out for people to take and all this unnecessary jazz.  I understand the drama with straws, to have or not to have. And to counter this I have several (sbucks branded, if that matters) reusable cold cups that I often use for planned trips to Starbucks. This trip was off the cuff.  Is Starbucks telling me that unless I have my own  cup/straw with me, I shouldn't bother visiting because I won't be able to enjoy my drink? I sincerely hope not.  I've been a pretty loyal fan of Starbucks and a gold card carrying member since what feels like forever. I've been to stores all over the world and this is the worst I've ever been treated.  I've never been left with such a sour taste in my mouth after it whilst visiting and I hope this encounter remains the exception to the rule.  PS. Did I mention my drink was terrible and it took more than five mins to get my piece of cake into a bag and out to me. My drink was out way before my bakery item was. Also not something I am used to.  PPS. I know, I know- first world problems. 🤷‍♀️🤦‍♀️
